<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-HKN-COYOTES-STARS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
TO STARS, IT'S DEJA BOO, AS COYOTES SCORE LATE FOR VICTORY
</HEADLINE>
 SIDEBAR-TEX (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By JEFF CAPLAN 
c.2000 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   DALLAS _ Dallas Drake couldn't explain his team's second dose of
late-game heroics against the NHL's premier defensive team.
</P>
<P>
   But his goal with less than three minutes to play helped the
Phoenix Coyotes defeat the Stars at Reunion Arena for the second
consecutive time.
</P>
<P>
   ``It was a great pass by \RJeremy Roenick\S,'' Drake said after
the 4-3 victory. ``I just tried to shoot it high.''
</P>
<P>
   He did, zipping the puck between Ed Belfour's glove and face
mask. Drake robbed the Stars of the momentum they had captured when
Mike Modano tied the score at 3-3 at the 9:52 mark. Roenick said
the Coyotes felt comfortable with the game tied, but emerged from
Modano's goal as the more aggressive offensive unit.
</P>
<P>
   ``You never sit back against this team; you never feel
comfortable against them,'' Roenick said. ``They play hard, and
they have a lot of power. We had to make sure we just kept at
them.''
</P>
<P>
   As the final period wore on and overtime looked to be on the
way, Roenick won possession of the puck along the boards in the
Stars' zone. He sent a centering pass to Drake, who was positioned
low in the left circle.
</P>
<P>
   ``It was a pass from the corner into the slot, a quick shot,''
goalie Ed Belfour said. ``It went in between my elbow and my
body.''
</P>
<P>
   The game winner sent grim reminders of the previous time the
Coyotes swept into town and stole two points with two goals late in
third period for a 3-2 victory Dec. 6.
</P>
<P>
   ``It just adds to our overall frustration against them knowing
that we've had opportunities to close them out and finish the game
and come from behind, and kind of take momentum away and take the
game away,'' Modano said. ``Those late goals are kind of
back-breakers. It's something that can really give teams a lot of
confidence.''
</P>
<P>
   The Coyotes fended off a possible six-point deficit and cut the
Stars' division to lead to two points. They finished with 20 shots
on goal and only six in the third period.
</P>
<P>
   Just 23 seconds prior to Drake's game winner, Belfour made a
save on a Shane Doan backhand, keeping him from a attaining a hat
trick after scoring goals in the first and second periods. But the
Coyotes weren't done.
</P>
<P>
   ``We kept working, kept working and we had a never-say-die
attitude,'' Roenick said. ``We knew we played a sound game all the
way through, and Dallas just made a fantastic shot. They beat us
twice in our building, and we've beaten them twice in their
building. We just went for it.'' nn
</P>
</TEXT>
