<P>
   GOODWILL-GAMES (Lake Placid, N.Y.) _ Jimmy Shea is riding a
major adrenaline high, he says. And it's not from his usual 80
mile-an-hour slide down a banked ice chute. Shea, a Lake Placid
resident and champion World Cup racer in a sliding sport known as
skeleton, has gone from alternately training and bartending to
being anointed something of a star for the 2000 Winter Goodwill
Games, Ted Turner's made-for-TV five-day multi-sport spectacle that
concludes Sunday.
</P>
