abolish the right of veteran public school teachers to demand a
hearing either before or after a school board's decision not to
re-hire them for the next school year. Gov. Roy Barnes is winning
his legislative battle to abolish tenure protection for all
teachers who start working for a Georgia school district after July
1, 2000. His plan is is far bolder than the limited attacks on
tenure by the governors of Colorado and Alabama, and goes further
than past attempts to ``abolish tenure'' in other states where
leaders claimed to abolish tenure, according to records at the
quasi-official Education Commission of the States and interviews
with scholars, state education officials and attorneys for school
boards and unions from coast to coast. They differ on whether the
change will help or hurt the state's schools. (Mollison, Cox News
Service). 30.
