   POLITICAL NEWS (``p'' category)
</P>
<P>
   SC-PRIMARY (Charleston, S.C.) _ South Carolina voters turned out
in record numbers Saturday to decide the hard-fought primary battle
between Texas Gov. George W. Bush and Sen. John McCain, R-Ariz., a
populist insurgent hoping to stage a second come-from-behind upset.
Bush needed victory to reassure worried supporters and prove he
remains electable in November after his surprise defeat in the New
Hampshire primary. McCain looked for an upset to catapult him into
success in Michigan's primary on Tuesday and to persuade
Republicans that his appeal to independents and Democrats gives the
GOP a better chance to recapture the White House in November. By
STEWART M. POWELL And DAN FREEDMAN.
</P>
